column1: Category:{{draft categories|[[category:drafts]]  [[Category:Bumping is back but only bump on Monday and Tuesday, this ensures deletion messages only come in on weekends where I have time to reasonably look over them  Previous bumping worked by adding [[:Category:wikipedia vdrafts]] but that was overused. So now addiing [[:Category:draft articles]] is the new one  As with the previous the idea behind this is that this designates any given draft to happen on a specific weekend day. A draft cannot be bumped twice, so they cannot end up floating to the top with being rebumped.  == Draft notes == Due to [[Wikipedia:Categories for discussion/Log/2023 July 21#Category:Secondary School Kanji]] almost all Joyo kanji here have the exact same expiration date. On January 8 they will all simultaneously go onto my talk page, and on February 8 they will all be simultaneously deleted.  I’ll have a later time around February 17 to March 17  where initially a glut of [[kyoiku kanji]] will come, followed by a lot of articles I bumped during the ani over the kanji, either over attempting to make them presentable and submittable or over bumping ones that would pop up in the weeks after October 22 so I’d have more time to get articles complete before getting bombarded with g13 deletions I’d no longer be able to stop.  On Monday November 27, 2023 I started bumping again These bumped articles will have their g17 warnings on Saturday April 27, 2024  I will bump again on Tuesday November 28, 2023,  These bumped articles will have their g17 warnings on Sunday April 28, 2024  I updated the draft table to the derived from tools one rather than the derived from talk page one, since enough were already bumped it was irrelevant that they came from the talk page  I needed to clear a large portion of drafts out so the page size limit was not exceeded. When I get my draft count down to 2,946 drafts I believe it will be good to have all drafts in the table. Definitely on January 8 redo this table  == [[User:Immanuelle]] ==  Generated using [https://xtools.wmcloud.org/pages/en.wikipedia.org/Immanuelle/118/noredirects/live XTools] on 2023-11-27 19:01  {| class="wikitable sortable" ! # !
